&gt; When you use web component with shadow DOM, the input elements within shadow DOM are not submitted with traditional form submission. Read here for [more details](https://github.com/w3c/webcomponents/issues/187).

In general, the only option is to introduce some JavaScript to submit your forms. The simple one I can think of is using [`FormData`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData/Using_FormData_Objects) when the submit event is triggered and then manually introspecting all the custom elements.

    function onSubmit() {


        const form = document.querySelector(&quot;form&quot;);

        const formData = new FormData();

        for (let x of form.elements) {
            formData.append(x.name,  x.value);
        }

        const customField = form.querySelector(&quot;my-lib&quot;);

        // Some way to access the custom form field&#39;s value
        formData.append(&quot;custom-field-name&quot;, customField.customValue);

        // Submit now
        // Write code to submit form using XHR or Fetch API
    }

To save some keystrokes you can avoid the for loop as you can create `FormData` using existing form:


    const form = document.querySelector(&quot;form&quot;);
    const formData = new FormData(form);

